The paper proposes a framework for cyber risk assessment and mitigation, which involves modeling attackers as formal planners and defenders as interdicting such plans. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the category of Computer Science and Cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper uses formal planning and prioritization techniques, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Game Theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the development of scalable algorithms, which is a common concern in Software Engineering (cs.SE) and System and Information Theory (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely categories for this paper are cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.SI, and cs.SE, in that order.
